title: $:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/profile-guide
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Understanding profiles

A //profile// is a small JSON document that tells JSON Convert how to
turn your source JSON into TiddlyWiki tiddlers.  It does two things,
and only two things:

* Picks which parts of the source become individual tiddlers
  (the ''records'').
* Describes, for each record, what the resulting tiddler's fields
  should look like (the ''bindings'').

That's the whole concept.  The rest of this guide is detail.

This is the canonical reference for profiles.  If you want a faster
start, the [[Console|$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/Console]] ships
with sample profiles you can open in the editor and learn from.  When
you want depth — what `..` means in a binding, why your custom
transform isn't showing in the picker, what `binding-token-star`
means — come back here.

''Contents''

* §1 What a profile looks like
* §2 Anatomy: `records`, `tw-fields`, `custom-fields`
* §3 Bindings
* §4 Path expressions
* §5 Transforms
